1
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:17,100
What is he doing here?

2
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:18,633
I love your daughter so much.

3
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:20,267
Let go of my daughter.

4
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:21,433
Get inside.

5
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:22,933
Are you leaving or not?

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,467
I saw everything, Auntie.

7
00:00:24,533 --> 00:00:26,800
I saw what Eden's mom
did to him.

8
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:28,867
I didn't betray you.

9
00:00:28,933 --> 00:00:30,833
I just fell in love.

10
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:32,700
Who do you love more?

11
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:34,333
Me or Red?

12
00:00:34,433 --> 00:00:37,100
Mom, I can love both of you.

13
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:38,433
No.

14
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:41,467
If you decide to choose him,
I will accept your decision.

15
00:00:41,533 --> 00:00:42,833
Even if it kills me.

16
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:45,000
Did you threaten to kill my son?

17
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:46,667
I just scared him off

18
00:00:46,733 --> 00:00:49,100
to stop him from bothering
my daughter.

19
00:00:49,167 --> 00:00:51,767
Perhaps you want me
to threaten you.

20
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:54,333
- Isn't that what you're doing?
- Zandro, show her

21
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,467
what you're about to throw
at her house.

22
00:00:58,033 --> 00:00:59,100
Mom!

23
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:01,833
- Uncle Zandro!
- Red, stay out of this.

24
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:03,167
Let's go home.

25
00:01:03,233 --> 00:01:04,600
Put that away. Come on!

26
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:06,833
Red, relax.

27
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,100
It's just a toy. See?

28
00:01:10,167 --> 00:01:11,967
You guys are crazy!

29
00:01:12,033 --> 00:01:13,767
- Stop messing with us!
- I just want to tell you

30
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:17,067
that I'm not giving up
on our relationship.

31
00:01:17,133 --> 00:01:19,733
Can you be happy
while our family's miserable?

32
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,500
Because I can't.

33
00:01:21,567 --> 00:01:25,200
After everything my mom
went through,

34
00:01:25,267 --> 00:01:26,867
I can sacrifice anything
for her,

35
00:01:26,933 --> 00:01:28,467
including our relationship.

36
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:49,267
So you're giving up on us...

37
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:50,300
again.

38
00:01:52,533 --> 00:01:53,633
Are you giving up?

39
00:01:57,567 --> 00:01:58,633
Red, I'm sorry.

40
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:03,100
I can't abandon my mom.

41
00:02:05,133 --> 00:02:09,433
And I can't choose anyone
over my mom.

42
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,267
Even if it's you.

43
00:02:17,567 --> 00:02:19,000
Let's stop this.

44
00:02:27,433 --> 00:02:29,067
Yen.

45
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:30,100
No.

46
00:02:31,867 --> 00:02:32,867
I won't let you do this.

47
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,300
We did everything to survive
on that island

48
00:02:38,367 --> 00:02:41,267
to fulfill our dreams.

49
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:44,833
Don't throw all of that away.

50
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:47,233
Red, I'm sorry.
But I've made my decision.

51
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,367
Just let me go.

52
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:51,700
So you don't care

53
00:02:51,767 --> 00:02:53,000
about everything
that we've been through.

54
00:02:54,667 --> 00:02:56,467
You'll throw all of that away.

55
00:02:57,733 --> 00:02:59,567
Red, can't you understand
where I'm coming from?

56
00:02:59,633 --> 00:03:01,833
Yen, can't you learn
to fight for me?

57
00:03:03,167 --> 00:03:04,600
Red, I can't do this anymore.

58
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,167
I can't bear
to see my mom suffer

59
00:03:08,233 --> 00:03:10,033
while loving the son
of the person

60
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:12,467
who ruined our lives.

61
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:13,667
I'm done, Red.

62
00:03:14,767 --> 00:03:16,933
Do you think it's easy for me
to end our relationship?

63
00:03:17,967 --> 00:03:19,467
It's hard for me too.

64
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:26,200
But I love my mom
more than I love you.

65
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:29,133
I'm sorry.

66
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:35,567
But we have to break up.

67
00:05:45,767 --> 00:05:47,367
Red?

68
00:05:47,433 --> 00:05:49,067
Red!

69
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:50,667
Hey, hey, hey. What's wrong?

70
00:05:50,733 --> 00:05:52,433
What's wrong?

71
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,467
What happened?

72
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:57,233
Yenyen and I are over.

73
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,767
She broke up with me.

74
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:03,067
Red, forget about her.

75
00:06:03,133 --> 00:06:05,367
She's not meant for you.

76
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,200
Eden!

77
00:06:17,267 --> 00:06:18,233
Eden!

78
00:06:19,267 --> 00:06:20,800
Raichu.

79
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:22,100
It hurts.

80
00:06:23,533 --> 00:06:25,167
I wanted to go back to him
earlier.

81
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:26,633
But I stopped myself...

82
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,733
from doing it.

83
00:06:31,167 --> 00:06:33,267
I wish I never fell in love.

84
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:39,800
Eden...

85
00:06:39,867 --> 00:06:42,400
it's not wrong to love someone.

86
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,767
You just love at the wrong time.

87
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:46,200
And the wrong person.

88
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,067
No, I need to fight for her.

89
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:50,567
I don't want to give up.

90
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,800
I understand.

91
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:57,100
But Red, it's hard to go
against fate.

92
00:06:58,533 --> 00:06:59,967
You know...

93
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:02,600
It's okay. Some people
are meant to fall in love

94
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:04,533
but not meant to be together.

95
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:08,267
You'll just get hurt.

96
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,567
Let her go. Forget her.

97
00:07:10,633 --> 00:07:12,467
Sab, I love her.

98
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:13,700
She's the one I love.

99
00:07:16,267 --> 00:07:20,900
Eden, love comes
in its own time.

100
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:24,067
We can't choose
whom to fall in love with.

101
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:26,967
And you can't say that Red
is not the right person for you.

102
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:30,133
I love my mom more.

103
00:07:31,467 --> 00:07:34,333
And we only have one mom.

104
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:37,933
I can't find another one
if I lose her.

105
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,300
That's why I'll take
every opportunity

106
00:07:41,367 --> 00:07:42,533
to make her happy.

107
00:07:44,467 --> 00:07:46,433
I can't be with Red anymore.

108
00:07:48,667 --> 00:07:51,200
I hate to say this to you,
but...

109
00:07:51,267 --> 00:07:52,333
What if...

110
00:07:53,667 --> 00:07:56,200
it's one-sided love?

111
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:57,833
Because if she loves you,

112
00:07:57,900 --> 00:08:00,067
she won't leave you
no matter what.

113
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:03,500
She left me because she didn't
want to hurt her mom.

114
00:08:04,867 --> 00:08:07,633
Then find someone to love
that will love you back.

115
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:10,700
Red, I'm here.

116
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:14,000
Here, it's okay.
I'll always be here.

117
00:08:14,067 --> 00:08:15,333
I'll never leave you.

118
00:08:17,633 --> 00:08:19,267
Stop crying. It's okay.

119
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:22,100
It's okay.

120
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:38,967
Mom!

121
00:08:40,967 --> 00:08:42,200
Mom...

122
00:08:42,267 --> 00:08:45,233
Don't hug me
after seeing that guy!

123
00:08:47,667 --> 00:08:49,200
Are you wondering
how I found out?

124
00:08:51,133 --> 00:08:52,900
- Mom.
- I overheard you.

125
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:55,867
I heard that you were meeting
with him.

126
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:57,167
Don't try to deny it.

127
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:59,367
Mom, it's true
that I met with him.

128
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:01,667
- But...
- Do whatever you want.

129
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:03,233
You're not a child anymore.

130
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,800
I won't stop you.

131
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:07,400
You can do whatever you want.

132
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:10,367
Who am I anyway?

133
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:14,767
I'm just a neglected mom.

134
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:17,467
Someone you can walk away
from even if she's hurting.

135
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,500
That's not true, Mom.

136
00:09:21,567 --> 00:09:24,300
I met with Red
to break up with him.

137
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,100
I chose you, Mom.

138
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:31,700
I don't want to see you hurt
anymore.

139
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:39,100
I don't want to waste
all the sacrifices

140
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:40,900
and love you gave me.

141
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:46,067
Mom, I know that no one
can love me as you do.

142
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,167
Mom...

143
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:52,433
You're irreplaceable.

144
00:09:58,767 --> 00:10:00,600
I'm sorry, Dear.

145
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,633
I thought you chose them
over me.

146
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:06,800
I'm sorry about everything
that I said.

147
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:10,000
Mom, I won't choose them
over you.

148
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:11,933
It's okay, Mom.

149
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:15,767
I know you said all of that
out of anger.

150
00:10:17,267 --> 00:10:19,267
Don't worry, Mom.

151
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:20,967
I'm going to forget Red.

152
00:10:27,633 --> 00:10:29,200
Stop crying.

153
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:48,967
Hon?

154
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:53,500
Hon, I was thinking...

155
00:10:53,567 --> 00:10:57,900
What if we just migrate
to the States?

156
00:10:57,967 --> 00:10:59,833
To get Red away from here.

157
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:03,633
We don't need to go anywhere.

158
00:11:04,767 --> 00:11:06,233
Yenyen and I broke up.

159
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:08,400
She broke up with me.

160
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,267
Are you happy now?

161
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:13,800
Red, you better watch
your tongue.

162
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:19,000
Look, Red, it's for the good
of everyone.

163
00:11:19,067 --> 00:11:23,467
Amanda and I can't accept
each other anyway.

164
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:30,000
And I can't bear to see you
with an ex-convict's daughter.

165
00:11:30,067 --> 00:11:31,200
Please.

166
00:11:31,267 --> 00:11:33,667
Please! I'm begging you.

167
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:35,400
Now that Yenyen and I
have broken up,

168
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:37,833
can you leave Amanda alone?

169
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:39,033
Hold on.

170
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:43,700
Why does it seem like
you're taking Amanda's side

171
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,300
instead of us?

172
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:46,967
Remember...

173
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:53,533
what we went through
because of that woman!

174
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,533
Leave her alone.

175
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,000
She's innocent.

176
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:59,000
You better watch your mouth!

177
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:02,300
She went to jail
because she committed a crime!

178
00:12:03,567 --> 00:12:06,933
And we will never forget
what she did!

179
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,467
Learn how to let go.

180
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:11,900
Let my brother rest in peace.

181
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:14,100
Let us all be at peace.

182
00:12:16,167 --> 00:12:19,533
My brother will never have peace
until we're peaceful.

183
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,900
Unbelievable.

184
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:46,000
There are a lot of stars
in the sky.

185
00:12:46,067 --> 00:12:48,200
It's only now that I appreciate
their beauty.

186
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:52,500
Lord, please.

187
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:54,567
Please.

188
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:55,733
Give me a sign.

189
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:10,933
Give me a sign that Red and I
are meant to be with each other.

190
00:13:19,133 --> 00:13:23,533
We were always busy
back in Manila.

191
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:25,633
There are a lot of distractions.

192
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:29,067
We never had time to stop...

193
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:31,767
to think...

194
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:33,867
to rest...

195
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:36,900
to chill...

196
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,333
And appreciate
the simple things.

197
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:47,200
But you know
what I appreciate most

198
00:13:47,267 --> 00:13:48,467
on this island?

199
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,267
It's having you here.

200
00:13:52,767 --> 00:13:53,733
Right now.

201
00:13:56,533 --> 00:13:58,933
If there's one good thing
that happened on this island...

202
00:14:02,233 --> 00:14:03,933
it's you.

203
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,467
Having found you...

204
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,467
knowing you.

205
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,900
Your boyfriend must be lucky.

206
00:14:19,933 --> 00:14:21,733
What? Are you serious?

207
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:24,100
Why did you have to ask God
for a sign?

208
00:14:24,167 --> 00:14:26,200
You broke up with him already!

209
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:28,433
It could be a sign that
we're not meant to be together.

210
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:31,900
Are you happy
with your decision?

211
00:14:31,967 --> 00:14:34,600
I'm happy now that my mom is
happy.

212
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:35,967
I'm not making her cry anymore.

213
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:37,433
I'm not asking about your mom.

214
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,333
I'm asking you.

215
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:42,400
Are you happy now
that you broke up with Red?

216
00:14:46,267 --> 00:14:47,833
See?

217
00:14:47,900 --> 00:14:49,000
You're not happy.

218
00:14:49,067 --> 00:14:51,033
You're miserable!

219
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,367
How about this?

220
00:14:52,433 --> 00:14:54,100
Beat your record.

221
00:14:54,167 --> 00:14:57,833
If you lose,
you and Red stay together.

222
00:14:57,900 --> 00:14:59,567
- Game?
- Okay, fine.

223
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:01,100
Okay.

224
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:03,367
Timer starts...

225
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:04,433
now!

226
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:22,633
Eden!

227
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:24,300
Eden!

228
00:15:24,367 --> 00:15:26,233
Eden!

229
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:29,800
Eden! Hey! Help her!

230
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:31,833
Help her!

231
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:46,700
Eden!

232
00:15:46,767 --> 00:15:48,000
Are you okay?

233
00:15:48,067 --> 00:15:49,167
- Hey, Eden!
- Ouch!

234
00:15:54,067 --> 00:15:55,633
What happened to you?

235
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:01,133
What happened?

236
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:04,233
I don't know, but I fainted
while I was swimming.

237
00:16:04,300 --> 00:16:05,900
I felt weak.

238
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:08,267
Raichu, help me.

239
00:16:08,367 --> 00:16:10,133
Let's go to the clinic.

240
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,233
Help us.

241
00:16:18,233 --> 00:16:19,833
Eden...

242
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:21,767
be careful.

243
00:16:21,833 --> 00:16:23,767
Just relax.

244
00:16:23,833 --> 00:16:25,567
Raichu, what happened?

245
00:16:25,633 --> 00:16:29,867
The last thing I remember
is I was swimming...

246
00:16:29,933 --> 00:16:30,967
then I felt dizzy.

247
00:16:31,033 --> 00:16:32,400
I know.

248
00:16:32,467 --> 00:16:34,633
You fainted while swimming.

249
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:36,467
You got me panicking.

250
00:16:39,067 --> 00:16:41,100
How are you feeling?

251
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,567
I'm okay.

252
00:16:43,967 --> 00:16:45,733
When was your last menstruation?

253
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:53,900
I'm okay.

254
00:16:53,967 --> 00:16:55,167
- Are you okay now?
- Yes.

255
00:16:55,233 --> 00:16:57,133
Thank you for your help.

256
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,967
Raichu, let's go.

257
00:16:59,033 --> 00:17:00,533
Are you sure?

258
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,033
Really?

259
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:04,133
You and Eden made up?

260
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:07,000
She said she broke up
with Rina's son.

261
00:17:10,700 --> 00:17:11,667
Really?

262
00:17:13,933 --> 00:17:15,900
Why do you look sad?

263
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,900
Aren't you supposed to be happy?

264
00:17:17,967 --> 00:17:20,600
Of course, I'm happy.

265
00:17:20,667 --> 00:17:23,633
I'm happy that the two of you
made up.

266
00:17:25,467 --> 00:17:30,867
But I know that Eden made
a sacrifice for you.

267
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,633
I know how painful it is
for her.

268
00:17:36,067 --> 00:17:40,400
We have to get hurt sometimes
to learn our lesson.

269
00:17:40,467 --> 00:17:42,933
That's why it happened to her.

270
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,600
Now she has realized that
her family is more important

271
00:17:45,667 --> 00:17:47,867
than loving the wrong person.

272
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:50,333
Someday when Eden becomes a mom,

273
00:17:50,433 --> 00:17:52,533
she'll understand
why I'm doing this.

274
00:17:58,800 --> 00:17:59,767
Eden...

275
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,200
did something happen
between you two on the island?

276
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:08,433
OMG!

277
00:18:10,067 --> 00:18:11,600
You must really love him.

278
00:18:12,833 --> 00:18:14,100
That's why I panicked
when the nurse asked me

279
00:18:14,167 --> 00:18:16,000
about my menstruation.

280
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:20,700
So are you really delayed
for a month?

281
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:24,500
Yes,
I still don't have my period.

282
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:25,700
Are you sure?

283
00:18:25,767 --> 00:18:28,133
Yes, I know the date.

284
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,633
It comes regularly.

285
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:32,500
Okay, okay.

286
00:18:33,467 --> 00:18:34,400
Let's not panic.

287
00:18:34,467 --> 00:18:36,400
Just relax, okay?

288
00:18:36,467 --> 00:18:37,433
I'll take care of this.

289
00:18:40,267 --> 00:18:41,633
What are we going to do?

290
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:09,667
Red...

291
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:14,067
Emma told me
that you haven't been eating

292
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,400
since yesterday.

293
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:19,833
I don't feel like eating.

294
00:19:23,933 --> 00:19:28,733
Well, maybe you and Eden
had a tough breakup.

295
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,100
Come on, speak up.

296
00:19:34,467 --> 00:19:37,567
You know you can talk to me
and your dad.

297
00:19:42,267 --> 00:19:44,833
I don't know, Mom.
I'm just so confused right now.

298
00:19:45,867 --> 00:19:47,033
You don't have to be.

299
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:51,900
You just have to open your eyes.

300
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:59,633
You know,
Sabina has always been around.

301
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:01,900
She's a nice girl.

302
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,133
I like her.

303
00:20:04,733 --> 00:20:07,300
Why don't you get back with her?

304
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:13,100
Mom, are you going to control
who I should love as well?

305
00:20:13,167 --> 00:20:16,433
Okay, I will stay out of it.

306
00:20:19,533 --> 00:20:26,133
Red, you know the right girl
will come at the right time...

307
00:20:27,633 --> 00:20:29,633
from the right family.

308
00:20:32,033 --> 00:20:34,100
Eden is out of the list.

309
00:20:39,933 --> 00:20:41,500
Come on, get up.

310
00:20:41,567 --> 00:20:42,900
Let's have something to eat.

311
00:20:42,967 --> 00:20:44,800
Let's have breakfast.

312
00:20:44,867 --> 00:20:46,100
Actually, it's brunch.

313
00:20:46,167 --> 00:20:48,033
Come on, let's have brunch.

314
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:49,300
I'll be right there.

315
00:20:50,433 --> 00:20:51,500
Okay.

316
00:21:11,167 --> 00:21:12,933
Do you have it now?

317
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,100
Are you sure that your mom
and aunt are not home?

318
00:21:15,167 --> 00:21:16,000
Yes, she won't be here
until later.

319
00:21:16,067 --> 00:21:17,900
My aunt's still at work.

320
00:21:17,967 --> 00:21:19,500
Okay, let's go to the bathroom.

321
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:27,500
What's that?
You dropped something.

322
00:21:31,733 --> 00:21:32,700
What's that?
You dropped something.

323
00:21:33,367 --> 00:21:34,867
I got it.

324
00:21:34,933 --> 00:21:36,633
You know...

325
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:38,867
it's a girl thing.

326
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:40,400
Shaving...

327
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:41,700
I was going to let you
borrow it but...

328
00:21:42,767 --> 00:21:44,200
I need to use it now.

329
00:21:44,267 --> 00:21:45,867
Oh, okay.

330
00:21:47,033 --> 00:21:49,600
- Fine.
- Mom, you're home early today.

331
00:21:49,667 --> 00:21:51,467
Someone bought
all my rice cakes.

332
00:21:51,533 --> 00:21:53,233
That's why I'm home early.

333
00:21:53,300 --> 00:21:55,033
That's good.

334
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:56,400
We're just going to go
to the bathroom, Mom.

335
00:21:56,467 --> 00:21:57,467
Okay.

336
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:00,267
Thank you.

337
00:22:32,233 --> 00:22:33,733
Will you marry me?

338
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:34,933
Yes!

339
00:22:54,533 --> 00:22:57,200
You're almost filled!

340
00:22:58,267 --> 00:23:02,300
I'll have enough
for Yenyen's enrollment.

341
00:23:10,833 --> 00:23:14,133
Eden, we need to wait
for two minutes.

342
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:16,200
I think I'm going to die
from anxiety.

343
00:23:17,867 --> 00:23:18,967
Eden...

344
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:23,000
We need to be negative
this time.

345
00:23:27,967 --> 00:23:31,100
Eden, I hope...

346
00:23:31,167 --> 00:23:33,767
I hope the second line
won't pop up.

347
00:23:42,567 --> 00:23:43,633
Raichu...

348
00:23:45,333 --> 00:23:46,633
I'm pregnant.

349
00:23:50,933 --> 00:23:51,933
Raichu...

350
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:55,500
I'm pregnant.

351
00:23:56,767 --> 00:23:58,000
I'm pregnant.

352
00:24:06,700 --> 00:24:08,500
Raichu.

353
00:24:08,567 --> 00:24:10,167
Raichu, what am I going to do?

354
00:24:13,767 --> 00:24:15,067
I booked your ticket.

355
00:24:15,133 --> 00:24:16,800
Everything is set.

356
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:18,733
You are leaving in two days.

357
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:21,433
- In two days?
- Why not?

358
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:23,100
Why aren't you touching
your food?

359
00:24:23,167 --> 00:24:24,667
I don't feel like eating.

360
00:24:24,733 --> 00:24:26,033
Yenyen loves to eat.

361
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:27,533
I'm not used to seeing her
not eating.

362
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:29,067
Thank you so much
for coming here

363
00:24:29,167 --> 00:24:30,900
at such short notice.

364
00:24:30,967 --> 00:24:33,600
I invited Sabina
to join us for dinner.

365
00:24:33,667 --> 00:24:35,233
It's Red's farewell party.

366
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:36,567
Why? What's going on?

367
00:24:36,633 --> 00:24:39,200
Don't you and Eden know?

368
00:24:39,267 --> 00:24:41,200
He's leaving today for the US.

369
00:24:41,267 --> 00:24:42,267
He's going to move there.

370
00:24:42,333 --> 00:24:43,933
Eden, he's leaving!

371
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,567
He's going to the US today!

372
00:24:45,633 --> 00:24:47,000
He'll be staying there for good!

373
00:24:47,067 --> 00:24:47,867
What?
